        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-06T16:02:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general we cannot depend in inputs being valid - if this gets deployed in any user-facing environment, just assume a fuzzer at the other end of the input stream 😊\n\n(actually I think we might even have a fuzzer for SVG, need to check)\n\nIf e.g. type\u003d\"matrix\" \u0026 values\u003d\"1 2 3\" I don\u0027t think we reject/validate in any way - so SkColorMatrix ends up reading beyond the allocated array (which may crash or not crash, or leak sensitive information etc).",
      "parentUuid": "72ce5e14_806f290e",
      "revId": "d9413b861ac1cef983592762b777faf4d2499196",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72c40059_5aefe4b8",
        "filename": "modules/svg/src/SkSVGFeColorMatrix.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 10818
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-06T16:12:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Gotcha, ok. Is the strategy to combine asserts + gracefully handling errors for non-debug builds, or just asserts?",
      "parentUuid": "29c94170_1e7345cf",
      "revId": "d9413b861ac1cef983592762b777faf4d2499196",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4bff4e75_d3c46d68",
        "filename": "modules/svg/src/SkSVGFeColorMatrix.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-06T16:23:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would say we have to handle anything that is sourced from .svg gracefully (we cannot assert anything about third-party data).\n\nthird party inputs (SVG files) -\u003e untrusted\nembedding client code (calling into our APIs) -\u003e trusted\n\nSo I don\u0027t think we need to be as careful about DOM API calls, same as we don\u0027t defend against clients passing garbage to Skia.  But the SVG inputs are potentially outside the client\u0027s control and requiring them to validate is unfeasible.",
      "parentUuid": "72c40059_5aefe4b8",
      "revId": "d9413b861ac1cef983592762b777faf4d2499196",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
